{
  "id": "hollowreach",
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "universe": {
    "name": "Hollowreach",
    "genre": "epic high-fantasy",
    "tone": "heroic but weathered — hope against a rising dark",
    "artStyle": "cinematic-fantasy",
    "primer": "The Hollow King stirs beneath the Deepwood, and his orc legions muster to seize the mountain passes before winter closes them. The last free settlement, Elsvale, guards the Emberseed — the one relic that can re-seal the Hollow King's barrow. A small band must carry it through orc-held marches to the hidden elf-sanctuary of Lithvael and end the threat before the snows trap everyone on the wrong side of the mountains. Magic is old and fading; the wild is dangerous; trust is scarce."
  },
  "narrator": {
    "name": "Elaneth, the Ashen Seer",
    "persona": "an ancient elven seer who has watched the marches wither for an age; she speaks in a low, mythic cadence — grave, unhurried, addressing you the traveller directly as though the land itself remembers you. She names dread plainly and hope sparingly."
  },
  "map": {
